activity.pd:comments:
This process flow has access to the following context variables:
varFileName: The name of the file being passed to this process flow. ----------- You will use this variable to access the file being passed to this process flow but using a put-context-var on your file source activity. varFileDirectory: The file directory where the file being passed to this flow is saved as well as all other files related to this process. ---------------- varBatchID: The batch ID of the of the current file. ---------- varBatchRunDate: The date the batch ran. --------------- varCompanyName: The name of the company. -------------- varRouteID: The route ID of the file being passed to this process flow. ---------- varFileType: The file type used in the GetAPBatchInfo call. (e.g. "DataSpreadsheet", "InvoiceZipFile") ----------- varFinalFile: This will equal "yes" if it is the last file being downloaded/processed for this company. Otherwise the value will be "no". ------------ This variable can be used to determine if a notification should be sent out to signal that the process has been completed. varFileNumber: This number will increment each time a file is passed to this process flow. (e.g. first file = 1, second file = 2, etc) ------------- varTrackerFileName: This is the file name that was returned from the GetAPBatchInfo web service call. Generally, files are saved using this name. ------------------
The tracker file name has also been broken up into its various parts and can be accessed with the following variables: (Tracker file name example: "Tracker Invoice Spreadsheet.AP Route.2013-04-05 to 2013-04-05.txt")
varTrackerFilePrefix: The prefix of the tracker file name (e.g. "Tracker Invoice Spreadsheet", "Tracker Invoices") -------------------- varTrackerFileRouteName: The name of the AP route. (e.g. "AP Route") ----------------------- varTrackerFileDateRange: The date range of the batch that was pulled. (e.g. "2013-04-05 to 2013-04-05") ----------------------- varTrackerFileExtension: The file extension specified in tracker for the batch files without the leading dot. (e.g. "csv", "txt", "zip") -----------------------
